2:T510,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between GitHub Copilot and an agentic coding tool like Cursor?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"GitHub Copilot is primarily an autocomplete tool — it suggests code as you type within your editor. Agentic coding tools like Cursor, Devin, or Claude Code can handle larger tasks autonomously: understanding a feature request, navigating the codebase, making changes across multiple files, and running tests."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Are AI coding agents safe to use with proprietary code?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"It depends on the tool. Cloud-based coding agents send code to external servers, which raises IP and privacy considerations. Some tools offer on-premise deployment or local models. Always review the data handling policy before using an AI coding agent with proprietary codebases."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can an AI coding agent work on any programming language?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most AI coding agents support the major languages well — Python, TypeScript, JavaScript, Go, Rust, Java. Performance on less common languages varies. Check the agent's documentation for specific language support."}}]}5:["slug","what-is-an-ai-coding-agent","d"]
